Rating: 3
Wow! I made this for a simple middle of the week dinner and was so pleased! My halibut fillets were thinner than 1 1/4 inch, and I did end up overcooking it slightly in order to get the browned effect. Would cook it less next time. If it is not cooked through with the original searing, don't distress the resting time and the heat from the topping will complete it. (better under than over). Secondly: Do not rush the saute of the shallots. The sweetness that they impart when caramelized makes the whole dish. I served it with butter sauteed asparagus that was accented with shallot and lemon peel as well.A really good meal. prepared in under an hour- most ingredients were already in my fridge/ pantry.

Rating: 4
Straightforward, healthful, delicious and easy. I can always make this by simply picking up fresh fish on the way home since I always have the rest on hand.

Rating: 4
Delicious, quick and easy! I was liberal with the pepper and salt in seasoning the fish, with the fresh lemon zest in the topping and squeezed lemon juice over the filet as we ate. I served it over the "Green" (herb) risotto from this website, using brown rice to keep it healthier. (The risotto took 40 minutes so I wouldn't recommend it unless you have time to spare.)

Rating: 3
Used most of the recipe ingredients, but cooked in a slightly different way. Dipped two filets first (1 1/2 lb total) in one whisked egg, then in flour seasoned with salt and pepper. Then placed in pre-heated olive oil on medium heat over the stove. Patted a mixture of 3/4 cup chopped pecans, 3/4 cup chopped parsley, 3/4 cup grated parmesan, 4 cloves of pressed garlic on top of each fillet, flipping after about 3 minutes and cooking on other side until flaky. Then placed the halibut on plate with foil. Scraped up bits from the pan, added one tablespoon butter, and sauteed the shallots with remaining bits of nuts and herbs, adding grated lemon zest at end, then topped the fish. Served with sauce from PECAN-CRUSTED TROUT WITH ORANGE-ROSEMARY BUTTER SAUCE on this site. Had fun cooking this together with my sister-in-law on a fish night, north shore of Boston, with the scallops and cilantro gremolata from here, and we had an incredibly happy and delicious feast with our families. Even my husband who doesn't like white fish loved it.

